    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTER AND COOLER - LUBRICATING
        OIL PUMP
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>LUBRICATING OIL PUMP</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the vibration damper as described in Section 7.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove front oil seal as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Mount front oil seal removal tool into crankshaft nose and over oil seal.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Turn forcing screw to remove seal.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the oil pump housing as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen and remove the six capscrews (two short capscrews are located at the two and
                        three o'clock positions). Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050904">9.4</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the oil pump housing with O-Ring seal from the front cover. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050905">9.5</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        . Discard the O-Ring seal.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the outer rotor from the oil pump drive spline. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050906">9.6</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050904" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2466" filename="../figeg2/EG2466.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.4.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Oil Pump Housing</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050905" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2467" filename="../figeg2/EG2467.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.5.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Oil Pump Housing</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. O-Ring</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050906" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2470" filename="../figeg2/EG2470.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.6.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Outer Rotor</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a hammer and chisel, remove the woodruff key from the crankshaft as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_199.xml" xrefid="ef1050907">9.7</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the inner rotor and oil slinger from the oil pump drive spline.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the oil pump housing plate. With the plate removed, remove the sealing O-Ring
                    from the front cover. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e105_199.xml" xrefid="ef1050908">9.8</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . Discard the O-Ring seal.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
